The paper discusses online algorithms, which are commonly studied in the computer science subfield of data structures (cs.DS). The focus on maximizing value and minimizing cost suggests that the paper may also fall under game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of randomness in the input permutation aligns with research in machine learning and stochastic processes (cs.LG), and the discussion of how the random-order model relates to other stochastic models suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC).
